"{\"uid\": \"en.tempo.co-read-1899132-todays-top-3-news-paris-2024-facts-about-turkeys-viral-olympic-shooter-yusuf-dikec\", \"text\": \"Editor  Laila Afifa  August 2, 2024 | 08:01 pm  TEMPO.CO,Jakarta-Tempo Englishcompiled the top three news on Friday, August 2, 2024. Here are the highlights: PARIS 2024: Facts About Turkey's Viral Olympic Shooter Yusuf Dikec, Indonesian Independence Day: Jokowi Leads National Prayer at Palace Tonight, and Indonesia's Bank Mandiri to Provide Integrated Digital Services for Golden Visa Program.  The following is the list of the top 3 news onTempo Englishtoday:  1. PARIS 2024: Facts About Turkey's Viral Olympic Shooter Yusuf Dikec  TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - Turkish Olympic shooter Yusuf Dikec has become a newfound Internet sensation for his cool and casual style. The marksman wore standard glasses, a team T-shirt and had his hand casually in his pocket, his face rather expressionless, as photos circulating on social media suggested.  Netizens called him an ordinary man who just happened to be competing in the Olympics, and some even compared his style to that of a killer. Meanwhile, Indonesian netizens described him as a \\\"housing complex dad.\\\"  Click here to read more  2. Indonesian Independence Day: Jokowi Leads National Prayer at Palace Tonight  TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - President Joko Widodo or Jokowi led a National Prayer at the Merdeka Palace, Jakarta this evening, August 1, 2024, as one of the series to kick off the commemoration of the 79th Indonesian Independence Day.  \\\"This is an annual event held every August 1. We are inviting approximately 3,163 people,\\\" said Deputy for Protocol and Presidential Secretariat Yusuf Permana via text message to Tempo on Thursday.  Click here to read more  3. Indonesia's Bank Mandiri to Provide Integrated Digital Services for Golden Visa Program  TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - The Directorate General of Immigration of the Ministry of Law and Human Rights officially launched Indonesia's Golden Visa on Thursday, July 25. Bank Mandiri, through Livin' by Mandiri was appointed as the first bank to provide integrated digital services for the golden visa program.  The Golden Visa program is expected to facilitate foreign investors to reside in Indonesia for 5 to 10 years. Foreigners could invest their funds through various means including in state-owned banks.  Click here to read more  Tempo.co  Recommended  World Cup 2026 Draw: Trump, Infantino and a Peace Prize  3 hours ago  10 Best World Cup Finals: The Most Memorable Matches in Football History  6 hours ago  Indonesia U-23 SEA Games 2025 Schedule: Philippines Await in Opener  1 days ago  Top 10 Best Football Managers in Europe in 25/26 Season  2 days ago  10 Oldest Players in World Cup History  3 days ago  2025 Thailand SEA Games Update: 11 Sports Venues Moved Due to Floods  4 days ago  Indonesia Unveils U-23 SEA Games Squad Featuring Four Diaspora Players  4 days ago  Flooding Forces Thailand to Move 10 SEA Games Sports to Bangkok  5 days ago  Indonesia Forward Hokky Caraka Aims to Settle Personal 'Debt' at SEA Games 2025  5 days ago  U-23 Indonesia Team Departs for Thailand on Friday for 2025 SEA Games  5 days ago  Today's Top 3 News: Prabowo Departs for Sumatra, 10 Best Places to Retire in US 2026  7 jam lalu  Here is the list of the top 3 news on Tempo English today.  Today's Top 3 News: Prabowo Departs for Sumatra to Inspect Disaster-Hit Areas  1 hari lalu  Here is the list of the top 3 news on Tempo English today.  Today's Top 3 News: 10 Best Places to Retire in US 2026, Affordable and Peaceful  2 hari lalu  Here is the list of the top 3 news on Tempo English today.  Today's Top 3 News: Prabowo Says Monitoring Sumatra Floods, Customer Reports Mirae Asset Sekuritas  3 hari lalu  Here is the list of the top 3 news on Tempo English today.  Today's Top 3 News:  M6.3 Megathrust Earthquake Strikes Aceh Amid Storm Aftermath  4 hari lalu  Here is the list of the top 3 news on Tempo English today.  Today's Top 3 News: Trop